verbLexeme: 1. To stir cream or eggs very fast until they are thick and frothy or stiff, especially using an egg-beater. English = whip.
2. To use an egg-beater. English = whip, beat.
nominalLexeme: 1. A kitchen tool with rotating blades used for beating eggs or whipping cream. English = egg-beater.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: operating an egg beater.
